By Aminu Garko Minna – The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has been commended over the successful conduct of Saturday’s Presidential and National Assembly Election. Dr Bashir Yankuzo, of the Department of Science Education, Federal
University of Science and Technology, Minna, gave the commendation on
Wednesday in Minna, in an interview with News Agency of Nigeria (NAN). The lecturer urged Nigerians to support President Muhammadu Buhari to succeed. He said the president would require maximum support to take Nigeria to greater heights. Yankuzu, who acknowledged that Nigeria was passing through hard
times, however, said with the support of all Nigerians, Buhari’s second
coming would ease the challenges. “I commend INEC, security agencies; and indeed the politicians for working together for the elections. “I hope and pray that they will improve in the forthcoming election for the overall development of our nascent democracy. “We thank God for the peaceful and successful conduct of 2019
Presidential and National Assembly elections and for a peaceful
political atmosphere before, during and after the elections,’’ he said. According to him, the current administration has provided a peaceful political atmosphere for a smooth electoral process. “It is my hope that the Federal Government will build on its
achievements, especially in areas of Security, anti-corruption,
agriculture and Job creations.’’ By Ibrahim Bello Birnin Kebbi - The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has declared President… Idowu Gabriel Ado-Ekiti - The Ekiti State chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has… By Ismaila Chafe Abuja - The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) on Monday in Abuja…